<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91262/189: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d546fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>,
                                on the same date to The Chargé in Germany as telegram No.
                                779.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-17T18:00:00-05:00">March 17,
                                    1941—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>803. For Paris. According to a D. N. B.<note n="2" xml:id="d546fn2">Deutsches Nachrichten Büro.</note> report Jay Allen, American
                            correspondent of the North American Newspaper Alliance, was <pb facs="0610" n="598" xml:id="pg_598"/> arrested together with another
                            unnamed American citizen while endeavoring to cross the demarcation line
                            between occupied and unoccupied France without correct papers.</p>
                        <p>Please investigate and submit prompt report.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>